<li id="cite_note-4"><b><a href="#cite_ref-4" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFM._Maltoni_.27.27et_al..27.272004">M. Maltoni <i>et al.</i> (2004). "Status of global fits to neutrino oscillations". <i>NJP</i> <b>06</b>: 122. <a href="/wiki/Digital_object_identifier" title="Digital object identifier">doi</a>:<span class="neverexpand"><a href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1088%2F1367-2630%2F6%2F1%2F122" class="external text" title="http://dx.doi.org/10.1088%2F1367-2630%2F6%2F1%2F122" rel="nofollow">10.1088/1367-2630/6/1/122</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Status+of+global+fits+to+neutrino+oscillations&amp;rft.jtitle=NJP&amp;rft.aulast=M.+Maltoni+%27%27et+al.%27%27&amp;rft.au=M.+Maltoni+%27%27et+al.%27%27&amp;rft.date=2004&amp;rft.volume=06&amp;rft.pages=122&amp;rft_id=info:doi/10.1088%2F1367-2630%2F6%2F1%2F122&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Neutrino"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> <a href="/wiki/ArXiv" title="ArXiv">arΧiv</a>:<a href="http://arxiv.org/abs/hep-ph/0405172" class="extiw" title="arxiv:hep-ph/0405172">hep-ph/0405172</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-PDG-5">^ <a href="#cite_ref-PDG_5-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-PDG_5-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREF.5B.5BParticle_Data_Group.5D.5D_.28S._Eidelman_.27.27et_al..27.27.292004"><a href="/wiki/Particle_Data_Group" title="Particle Data Group">Particle Data Group</a> (S. Eidelman <i>et al.</i>) (2004). "<a href="http://pdg.lbl.gov/2005/listings/lxxx.html" class="external text" title="http://pdg.lbl.gov/2005/listings/lxxx.html" rel="nofollow">Leptons in the 2005 Review of Particle Physics</a>". <i>Phys. Lett. B</i> <b>592</b> (1): 1–5<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://pdg.lbl.gov/2005/listings/lxxx.html" class="external free" title="http://pdg.lbl.gov/2005/listings/lxxx.html" rel="nofollow">http://pdg.lbl.gov/2005/listings/lxxx.html</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2007-11-25</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Leptons+in+the+2005+Review+of+Particle+Physics&amp;rft.jtitle=Phys.+Lett.+B&amp;rft.aulast=%5B%5BParticle+Data+Group%5D%5D+%28S.+Eidelman+%27%27et+al.%27%27%29&amp;rft.au=%5B%5BParticle+Data+Group%5D%5D+%28S.+Eidelman+%27%27et+al.%27%27%29&amp;rft.date=2004&amp;rft.volume=592&amp;rft.issue=1&amp;rft.pages=1%E2%80%935&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fpdg.lbl.gov%2F2005%2Flistings%2Flxxx.html&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Neutrino"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-6"><b><a href="#cite_ref-6" title="">^</a></b> Since neutrino flavor <a href="/wiki/Eigenstates" title="Eigenstates" class="mw-redirect">eigenstates</a> are not the same as neutrino mass eigenstates (see <a href="/wiki/Neutrino_oscillation" title="Neutrino oscillation">neutrino oscillation</a>), the given masses are actually mass <a href="/wiki/Expectation_value" title="Expectation value" class="mw-redirect">expectation values</a>. If the mass of a neutrino could be measured directly, the value would always be that of one of the three mass eigenstates: ν<sub>1</sub>, ν<sub>2</sub>, and ν<sub>3</sub>. In practice, the mass cannot be measured directly. Instead it is measured by looking at the shape of the endpoint of the energy spectrum in particle decays. This sort of measurement directly measures the expectation value of the mass; it is not sensitive to any of the mass eigenstates separately.</li>
<li id="cite_note-PhysRevD-7">^ <a href="#cite_ref-PhysRevD_7-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-PhysRevD_7-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFKaragiorgiA._Aguilar-Arevalo.2C_J._M._Conrad.2C_and_M._H._Shaevitz2007">Karagiorgi, G.; A. Aguilar-Arevalo, J. M. Conrad, and M. H. Shaevitz (2007). "<a href="http://scitation.aip.org/getabs/servlet/GetabsServlet?prog=normal&amp;id=PRVDAQ000075000001013011000001&amp;idtype=cvips&amp;gifs=yes" class="external text" title="http://scitation.aip.org/getabs/servlet/GetabsServlet?prog=normal&amp;id=PRVDAQ000075000001013011000001&amp;idtype=cvips&amp;gifs=yes" rel="nofollow">Leptonic CP violation studies at MiniBooNE in the (3+2) sterile neutrino oscillation hypothesis</a>". <i><a href="/wiki/Physical_Review" title="Physical Review">Phys Rev</a> D</i> <b>75</b> (013011): 1–8. <a href="/wiki/Digital_object_identifier" title="Digital object identifier">doi</a>:<span class="neverexpand"><a href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1103%2FPhysRevD.75.013011" class="external text" title="http://dx.doi.org/10.1103%2FPhysRevD.75.013011" rel="nofollow">10.1103/PhysRevD.75.013011</a></span><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://scitation.aip.org/getabs/servlet/GetabsServlet?prog=normal&amp;id=PRVDAQ000075000001013011000001&amp;idtype=cvips&amp;gifs=yes" class="external free" title="http://scitation.aip.org/getabs/servlet/GetabsServlet?prog=normal&amp;id=PRVDAQ000075000001013011000001&amp;idtype=cvips&amp;gifs=yes" rel="nofollow">http://scitation.aip.org/getabs/servlet/GetabsServlet?prog=normal&amp;id=PRVDAQ000075000001013011000001&amp;idtype=cvips&amp;gifs=yes</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Leptonic+CP+violation+studies+at+MiniBooNE+in+the+%283%2B2%29+sterile+neutrino+oscillation+hypothesis&amp;rft.jtitle=%5B%5BPhysical+Review%7CPhys+Rev%5D%5D+D&amp;rft.aulast=Karagiorgi&amp;rft.aufirst=G.&amp;rft.au=Karagiorgi%2C+G.&amp;rft.au=A.+Aguilar-Arevalo%2C+J.+M.+Conrad%2C+and+M.+H.+Shaevitz&amp;rft.date=2007&amp;rft.volume=75&amp;rft.issue=013011&amp;rft.pages=1%E2%80%938&amp;rft_id=info:doi/10.1103%2FPhysRevD.75.013011&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fscitation.aip.org%2Fgetabs%2Fservlet%2FGetabsServlet%3Fprog%3Dnormal%26id%3DPRVDAQ000075000001013011000001%26idtype%3Dcvips%26gifs%3Dyes&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Neutrino"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-8"><b><a href="#cite_ref-8" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFAlpert2007">Alpert, M. (August 2007). "<a href="http://www.sciam.com/article.cfm?chanID=sa006&amp;colID=5&amp;articleID=B5CB9C67-E7F2-99DF-3BF7368614D46C5D" class="external text" title="http://www.sciam.com/article.cfm?chanID=sa006&amp;colID=5&amp;articleID=B5CB9C67-E7F2-99DF-3BF7368614D46C5D" rel="nofollow">Dimensional Shortcuts</a>". <i>Scientific American</i><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.sciam.com/article.cfm?chanID=sa006&amp;colID=5&amp;articleID=B5CB9C67-E7F2-99DF-3BF7368614D46C5D" class="external free" title="http://www.sciam.com/article.cfm?chanID=sa006&amp;colID=5&amp;articleID=B5CB9C67-E7F2-99DF-3BF7368614D46C5D" rel="nofollow">http://www.sciam.com/article.cfm?chanID=sa006&amp;colID=5&amp;articleID=B5CB9C67-E7F2-99DF-3BF7368614D46C5D</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Dimensional+Shortcuts&amp;rft.jtitle=Scientific+American&amp;rft.aulast=Alpert&amp;rft.aufirst=M.&amp;rft.au=Alpert%2C+M.&amp;rft.date=August+2007&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciam.com%2Farticle.cfm%3FchanID%3Dsa006%26colID%3D5%26articleID%3DB5CB9C67-E7F2-99DF-3BF7368614D46C5D&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Neutrino"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
